Many people were left captivated after watching a music video collaborated between the Drakensberg Boys Choir and Sharks rugby team. Following the success of the original Follow You video, the school said the Sharks rugby team reached out to the choir to do a collaboration, bringing the two different worlds of sport and art together. The video currently has over 86 000 views on Facebook and over 9 000 views on YouTube. It has been shared over 1 900 times and has left people holding back tears after watching the heart-warming music video. Commenting on the Drakensberg Boys Choir, Linda Dillon wrote, “Openly weeping. This is the South Africa I believe in and why I will never leave. Thank you to the Sharks team and the Drakensberg Boys Choir. Together we can.” Anu Muirhead wrote, “And from a granny in Cape Town (and Alan Stuart’s aunty) I write to say I have tears in my eyes. Heartening stuff. Love the upbeat rhythm and song dear Drakensberg Boys - so so proud of you.” Jeremy J'emz Govender said, “Absolutely brilliant. Well done boys. You make us so proud.”